==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Irreversible steering gear
<hw>Ir`re*vers"i*ble steering gear</hw>. <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A
steering gear, esp. for an automobile, not affected by the road wheels,
as when they strike an obstacle side ways, but easily controlled by the
hand wheel or steering lever.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Irreversibly</ent>⟦br⟧
